    <h2>About Us</h2>
    <p>Nike is a global leader in athletic footwear, apparel, equipment, and accessories. Founded on January 25, 1964, as Blue Ribbon Sports by Bill Bowerman and Phil Knight, the company officially became Nike, Inc. in 1971, named after the Greek goddess of victory. Its iconic "Swoosh" logo and the slogan "Just Do It" are among the most recognized branding elements in the world.

        Headquartered in Beaverton, Oregon, Nike designs and markets a wide range of products for sports like running, basketball, soccer, and lifestyle wear. The company is known for innovation in both performance and style, regularly collaborating with athletes and designers. It also owns popular sub-brands like Jordan and Converse.
        
        Nike continues to influence not just sportswear, but also streetwear, pop culture, and global fashion — blending performance and style in a way few brands can match.
        
        
        
